lessons.content:
C# supports various data types like int, double, string, and bool.

Example:
```csharp
int age = 25;
string name = "Alice";
bool isStudent = true;
```

Control structures like if, for, and while manage the flow of a C# program.

Example:
```csharp
if (age > 18) {
  Console.WriteLine("Adult");
} else {
  Console.WriteLine("Minor");
}
```

